doc:(text body) contains the whole body of a single unitary text, excluding any front or back matter. [4. ]

doc:(1) a heading, title etc. attached to a picture or diagram; (2) a pull quote or other text about or extracted from a text and superimposed upon it to draw attention to it. []

doc:(document author) contains the name of the author of the document, as given on the title page (often but not always contained in a byline). [4.6. ]
doc:(document edition) contains an edition statement as presented on a title page of a document. [4.6. ]
doc:(document imprint) contains the imprint statement (place and date of publication, publisher name), as given (usually) at the foot of a title page. [4.6. ]
